This paper focuses on improving ranking results for web search, specifically in the context of recency search. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests a potential fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of real-time adaptation of user clicks, which could potentially fit with cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
